cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.CY 

The paper is about predicting human behavior in games, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT). The use of different models to predict human behavior also suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The Bayesian analysis mentioned in the abstract suggests the use of statistical inference (cs.SI), and the evaluation of model variants suggests the involvement of computational complexity (cs.CY).
